09:12.226 --> 09:14.797
Your father's told me so much about you,

09:14.830 --> 09:17.333
Evan, and your sister, Emma.

09:17.365 --> 09:18.833
Didn't see that one coming.

09:19.967 --> 09:22.537
But, you, concierge doctor to the stars?

09:22.571 --> 09:24.273
That's not exactly...

09:24.306 --> 09:25.840
You know what, he's just being modest.

09:25.874 --> 09:26.841
It's like a sickness.

09:26.874 --> 09:27.909
Speaking of which,

09:27.942 --> 09:30.178
I think that Annette
needs one of your exams.

09:30.211 --> 09:33.215
I do not need an exam.

09:33.248 --> 09:34.682
Ms. Newberg and I are very worried

09:34.715 --> 09:37.152
what with all of the events
coming up for the wedding.

09:37.185 --> 09:39.488
So, Annette, what's going on?

09:39.520 --> 09:41.389
Ask Mr. Doctor over there.

09:41.422 --> 09:43.859
She has trouble hearing,
she has trouble sleeping,

09:43.892 --> 09:45.060
and she's weak.

09:45.092 --> 09:48.129
- Am I right?
- Welcome to life in your 60s.

09:48.162 --> 09:50.099
Uh-huh.

09:50.132 --> 09:53.068
70s?

09:53.100 --> 09:55.837
Anyway, how about you
let me draw some blood,

09:55.870 --> 09:57.706
get some more of your
history, and do a CT?

09:57.739 --> 09:59.807
Just to make sure Mr.
Doctor here isn't right.

09:59.840 --> 10:01.744
Fine.

10:01.777 --> 10:05.913
But these symptoms are probably
just from my hearing aids.

10:05.946 --> 10:07.715
I think the batteries died.

10:07.749 --> 10:09.984
Easy peasy. He can fix them.

10:10.018 --> 10:12.254
Uh, Dad, you don't fix
batteries, you replace them.

10:12.287 --> 10:13.922
But if anybody can do it, you can do it.

10:13.955 --> 10:17.626
He takes household items
and makes medical devices.

10:17.658 --> 10:19.427
I'm not kidding. He's
like that guy on TV.

10:19.460 --> 10:21.062
What is that guy's name?
What is the guy's name?

10:21.095 --> 10:22.597
Mr. Fix It?

10:22.630 --> 10:24.298
Mr. Fix It. You're Mr. Fix it.

10:24.331 --> 10:26.402
Okay. I'm Mr. Fix it.

10:32.541 --> 10:35.010
You're amazing.

10:35.042 --> 10:36.010
These should be in a museum,

10:36.043 --> 10:38.880
not dragged over dirt and asphalt.

10:38.913 --> 10:41.850
I want the newlyweds to
drive away in style.

10:41.883 --> 10:42.917
Thank you for helping.

10:42.951 --> 10:45.053
I know you're not doing it for him.

10:51.826 --> 10:54.696
I can't wait. I'm too excited.

10:54.730 --> 10:55.964
What's wrong with a heads-up?

10:55.997 --> 10:58.233
- The blood test is tomorrow.
- I know. So what?

10:58.265 --> 10:59.267
If we're gonna be pregnant tomorrow,

10:59.301 --> 11:01.903
we're already pregnant today, so...

11:01.936 --> 11:03.538
It's like peeking at the end
of a book before you read it.

11:03.571 --> 11:05.673
- Everyone does it.
- I don't.

11:05.706 --> 11:07.975
Then how do you know
what's gonna happen?

11:08.009 --> 11:09.143
Please?

11:09.177 --> 11:12.181
All right. We'll wait.

11:19.955 --> 11:21.724
Thanks for teaching me to dance.

11:21.757 --> 11:23.392
- Straight line?
- Uh-huh.

11:23.425 --> 11:26.061
- Straight line.
- All right.

11:26.094 --> 11:30.199
Rectangle and triangle.

11:30.231 --> 11:31.199
You're good at this.

11:31.233 --> 11:33.135
- You must practice.
- Uh-huh.

11:33.167 --> 11:35.604
Do you, uh, have a partner
you go out and dance with?

11:35.637 --> 11:37.272
No.

11:37.305 --> 11:38.340
It's like riding a bike,

11:38.373 --> 11:40.342
just to music and with no pedaling.

11:40.374 --> 11:42.277
Ah.

11:42.310 --> 11:44.613
I only ask because I saw that
woman at the lab yesterday.

11:44.645 --> 11:46.147
She seemed excited to see you.

11:46.181 --> 11:47.249
- I thought...
- Rectangle.

11:47.282 --> 11:49.718
Mm-hmm.

11:49.750 --> 11:51.385
Okay, I know her name is C.G.

11:51.418 --> 11:52.821
and that she's a HankMed patient.

11:52.854 --> 11:54.889
Cindy, really, was a HankMed patient.

11:54.922 --> 11:57.525
We're... we're doing research together.

11:57.558 --> 11:58.893
Ah.

12:01.997 --> 12:03.899
But I-I like her.

12:03.932 --> 12:05.533
I'm so happy for you.

12:05.566 --> 12:08.336
She's very... very smart,

12:08.369 --> 12:10.873
uh, and talented and accomplished.

12:10.906 --> 12:12.274
I hope she likes me.

12:12.307 --> 12:14.109
Well, you're all those
things too, Jeremiah,

12:14.142 --> 12:16.345
and I'm sure she will.

12:16.378 --> 12:18.213
You're quite the catch, you know...

12:18.245 --> 12:20.515
single, smart, doctor.

12:20.548 --> 12:22.683
Just like you.

12:22.716 --> 12:24.619
Straight line.

12:25.854 --> 12:27.656
You bringing her to the wedding?

12:27.688 --> 12:29.690
Uh, Cindy doesn't really like crowds,

12:29.724 --> 12:31.460
and anyway, I don't have a plus one.

12:31.493 --> 12:33.128
Look at you.

12:33.161 --> 12:35.297
It's all coming clear now.

12:35.330 --> 12:36.999
What? No, no. It's not...

12:37.032 --> 12:38.133
Hi, Jeremiah.

12:38.166 --> 12:40.469
Or should I say the future Mr.
Henry Lawson?

12:40.502 --> 12:42.037
- Dad.
- Hi, Eddie.

12:42.070 --> 12:45.840
- Good effort.
- Thanks.

12:45.874 --> 12:47.909
- I've got great news.
- What?

12:47.942 --> 12:50.545
It's not Mr. Fix it. It's MacGyver.

12:50.579 --> 12:52.414
Please tell me you didn't
drive here to tell me that.

12:52.446 --> 12:53.682
I didn't drive here to tell you that.

12:53.715 --> 12:55.450
- Good.
- It's about your brother Evan.

12:55.483 --> 12:57.753
Look, I don't want his
anger to affect his toast

12:57.786 --> 12:58.987
at the rehearsal dinner.

12:59.019 --> 13:01.122
No matter how he feels about me,

13:01.156 --> 13:04.059
his anger should not
affect my bride-to-be.

13:04.091 --> 13:06.494
It's her sixth wedding.
It should be perfect.

13:06.528 --> 13:07.796
All right, don't worry. Okay?

13:07.829 --> 13:09.263
I will make sure Evan behaves.

13:09.297 --> 13:10.666
How?

13:10.699 --> 13:11.667
I don't know.

13:11.700 --> 13:13.701
I'll MacGyver it.

13:13.734 --> 13:15.970
You smarty-pants.

13:34.388 --> 13:36.457
Look, it's part of our responsibilities

13:36.490 --> 13:38.893
and the honor of being Best Men.

13:38.927 --> 13:40.995
Oh, my God, responsibility and honor.

13:41.028 --> 13:43.264
The fact that you're even using
those two words in a sentence

13:43.297 --> 13:44.799
about Dad is hilarious.

13:44.832 --> 13:46.267
It's ridiculous! Come on.

13:46.301 --> 13:47.603
He deserted us.

13:47.635 --> 13:50.338
He stole money from HankMed.
He sold Boris out.

13:50.372 --> 13:53.041
Like, why would I want a
person like that in my life?

13:53.074 --> 13:54.509
Because people change.

13:54.542 --> 13:55.944
Dad's changed.

13:55.976 --> 13:57.812
Look, he's starting a new life,

13:57.845 --> 13:58.946
he's gonna need our support.

13:58.980 --> 13:59.947
Yeah, well...

13:59.980 --> 14:01.148
I get it, you're upset.

14:01.182 --> 14:02.316
Yeah, I don't think you do.

14:02.350 --> 14:04.485
Look, I'm going. I will
go to the wedding.

14:04.518 --> 14:06.355
I will dance at the wedding,

14:06.388 --> 14:07.989
but I will not give a toast tonight.

14:08.023 --> 14:09.358
- Ugh!
- ♪ For too long ♪

14:09.390 --> 14:12.126
♪ I've been keeping
this family together ♪

14:12.159 --> 14:14.528
Whose family would that be?

14:14.561 --> 14:18.432
♪ For too long I've been
the responsible one ♪

14:18.465 --> 14:21.135
I'm sorry. What?

14:21.168 --> 14:25.606
♪ Now you want me to stand
there all smiles and giggles ♪

14:25.639 --> 14:26.908
Sorry.

14:26.941 --> 14:27.909
♪ I'm done ♪

14:27.942 --> 14:28.943
Okay.

14:30.744 --> 14:34.383
♪ For too long, you've lived
every day unaffected ♪

14:34.416 --> 14:36.984
Yeah, well, I am a CPA.

14:37.018 --> 14:38.186
♪ For too long ♪

14:38.219 --> 14:40.455
♪ For Evan it's fun in the sun ♪

14:40.488 --> 14:43.358
By "fun," you mean building
our business, right?

14:43.390 --> 14:44.592
♪ And, excuse me ♪

14:44.625 --> 14:46.861
♪ I've kept this family together ♪

14:46.894 --> 14:48.663
That's right. Me!

14:48.696 --> 14:50.298
♪ But I'm done ♪

14:50.331 --> 14:51.732
♪ I'm done ♪

14:51.765 --> 14:55.436
♪ I'm done ♪

14:55.470 --> 14:57.873
♪ Yes, I'm done and done and done ♪

14:57.906 --> 15:00.275
♪ I'm through with pretending ♪

15:00.307 --> 15:01.976
That's great.

15:03.008 --> 15:04.178
♪ I'm done and done and done ♪

15:04.211 --> 15:07.950
♪ You can't cure that, son ♪

15:07.983 --> 15:10.518
♪ Yeah, I'm done
and done and done ♪

15:10.552 --> 15:13.888
♪ This chapter is ending ♪

15:13.922 --> 15:16.624
♪ I'm done ♪

15:18.092 --> 15:21.195
♪ Even so, as you go and
leave this behind ♪

15:21.229 --> 15:24.533
♪ Here's a thing that I pray
will weigh on your mind ♪

15:24.566 --> 15:27.101
♪ This could be your
last memory of Dad ♪

15:27.134 --> 15:30.672
♪ Your last gift as his son ♪

15:30.705 --> 15:31.739
♪ Thank you, no ♪

15:31.773 --> 15:33.742
♪ I'm passing it, I'm okay ♪

15:33.774 --> 15:34.942
♪ Hank, you know ♪

15:34.975 --> 15:37.111
♪ You can't Hank me this time, no way ♪

15:37.144 --> 15:40.581
♪ I can see that you don't
really listen a ton ♪

15:40.614 --> 15:42.249
- Evan.
- ♪ I'm done ♪

15:42.283 --> 15:44.385
- Evan.
- ♪ I'm done ♪

15:44.418 --> 15:46.120
All right, I get it.

15:46.153 --> 15:48.590
♪ You're done and done and done ♪

15:48.623 --> 15:50.624
♪ And yet you're still singing ♪

15:50.658 --> 15:51.994
Oh, my God.

15:52.027 --> 15:54.662
♪ Though I'm done and done and done ♪

15:54.696 --> 15:58.367
♪ I've only begun ♪

15:58.399 --> 16:01.168
♪ I'm done and done and done ♪

16:01.201 --> 16:06.274
- ♪ You're done ♪
- ♪ I'm done ♪

16:08.976 --> 16:10.478
- Evan?
- No.

16:12.379 --> 16:14.215
- Evan.
- No.

16:15.582 --> 16:18.019
Evan.

16:18.052 --> 16:19.754
Fine, I'll do it.

16:21.789 --> 16:23.090
Sorry for interrupting.

16:23.124 --> 16:25.694
No, no, no, not at all.
Is everything okay?

16:25.726 --> 16:27.194
- You can...
- Oh, yeah.

16:27.228 --> 16:29.931
Nice to see you again.

16:29.964 --> 16:32.801
I don't make a habit of
breaking and entering,

16:32.834 --> 16:36.805
though I did play a cat
burglar for Hitch once.

16:36.837 --> 16:39.240
It was a second-story job,

16:39.273 --> 16:43.644
and the diamonds were concealed
in a cut crystal decanter

16:43.677 --> 16:46.447
of the finest Canadian whiskey.

16:46.480 --> 16:48.115
Huh.

16:48.148 --> 16:51.519
Annette, is something wrong?

16:51.552 --> 16:53.554
Hmm?

16:53.587 --> 16:55.656
Oh, right. Oh.

16:55.690 --> 16:57.993
Those symptoms your father said I had,

16:58.026 --> 16:59.995
he's smarter than he looks.

17:00.028 --> 17:00.995
Hmm.

17:01.028 --> 17:02.463
Why didn't you tell me before?

17:02.497 --> 17:04.132
It's none of your business.

17:04.164 --> 17:05.465
Okay.

17:05.499 --> 17:08.737
And because I don't want it to be true.

17:08.769 --> 17:10.204
My memory's all funny.

17:10.238 --> 17:15.810
I can't remember how to get
to the theater sometimes.

17:15.844 --> 17:17.045
Can't even remember the cocktails
that I had last night.

17:17.077 --> 17:19.314
It's Alzheimer's,

17:19.346 --> 17:22.782
an ugly name for an ugly disease.

17:22.816 --> 17:25.752
Look, memory loss can be a
symptom of a lot of things,

17:25.787 --> 17:28.522
like lack of sleep, too many cocktails,

17:28.556 --> 17:30.659
or even old age.

17:30.691 --> 17:34.462
Not that you're old or drink too much.

17:34.496 --> 17:35.864
How's your sleep?

17:35.896 --> 17:37.331
I've never been a good sleeper...

17:37.364 --> 17:40.134
- too much to do, until now.
- Mm.

17:40.168 --> 17:42.037
I'll have to quit the show,

17:42.069 --> 17:44.605
quit the business.

17:44.639 --> 17:48.543
It's been my life since I was 19.

17:48.576 --> 17:49.778
Mm.

17:49.810 --> 17:51.712
Have you had trouble remembering
things from your past?

17:51.746 --> 17:53.648
Just new things,

17:53.681 --> 17:55.450
like my lines for the play.

17:55.482 --> 17:58.286
I just stand there like a half-wit.

17:58.318 --> 18:00.055
It's called anterograde memory loss,

18:00.087 --> 18:03.624
and while, yes, that might
be a symptom of Alzheimer's,

18:03.657 --> 18:04.892
you might be suffering from something

18:04.925 --> 18:06.694
that's completely reversible,

18:06.728 --> 18:09.831
like encephalopathy or dehydration.

18:09.864 --> 18:12.334
So let's wait till the
test results come back

18:12.366 --> 18:13.902
before we worry too much.

18:13.934 --> 18:16.037
It's gonna be okay.

18:20.674 --> 18:23.177
Hey, Rembrandt.

18:23.210 --> 18:25.180
Wow, what's that for?

18:25.212 --> 18:26.514
It's for your wedding.

18:26.547 --> 18:28.849
It's for guests to write
their wishes to your guys,

18:28.883 --> 18:30.719
so you'll always know how
many people love you.

18:30.751 --> 18:32.052
What a great thought.

18:32.085 --> 18:33.454
It looks just like the photograph.

18:33.488 --> 18:36.024
Thanks.

18:36.057 --> 18:37.025
Okay, what's wrong?

18:37.057 --> 18:38.192
What do you mean?

18:38.226 --> 18:39.861
It's Eddie. Spill.

18:39.893 --> 18:41.662
I'm fine.

18:41.695 --> 18:43.330
I really don't know what
you're talking about.

18:43.364 --> 18:44.432
- You don't?
- No.

18:44.464 --> 18:46.801
Would you step inside my office, please?

18:50.371 --> 18:51.540
Come here.

18:57.545 --> 18:59.848
All right, what gives?

19:02.849 --> 19:04.718
I'm not pregnant.

19:04.751 --> 19:06.187
Sweetie.

19:06.220 --> 19:09.124
And I'm afraid I never will be.

19:09.156 --> 19:11.025
I just...

19:11.058 --> 19:12.893
don't understand why something
that's supposed to be

19:12.926 --> 19:15.129
so simple has to be so hard.

19:15.162 --> 19:18.967
Okay, listen, I am the perfect example

19:18.999 --> 19:22.703
of how simple gets complicated.

19:22.737 --> 19:24.573
You don't give up.

19:24.605 --> 19:26.907
Now I know why Evan is so upset.

19:26.941 --> 19:28.210
Oh, no, he doesn't know.

19:28.242 --> 19:30.644
Just the thought of telling him...

19:30.678 --> 19:31.880
he's gonna just be...

19:31.912 --> 19:34.348
I know, I know, I know, I know.

19:34.382 --> 19:35.984
I know very few things.

19:36.017 --> 19:37.719
This I know for sure,

19:37.751 --> 19:42.323
one day, you are going
to be a fantastic mom.

19:42.356 --> 19:44.291
Do you believe me?

19:44.325 --> 19:47.729
Do you believe me? Come here.

19:47.761 --> 19:50.264
I promise.

19:52.467 --> 19:55.604
Wow, are you a good painter.

19:55.636 --> 19:57.806
Could you make my teeth smaller?

20:03.918 --> 20:05.720
Hi.

20:05.754 --> 20:07.689
Hi.

20:07.930 --> 20:09.398
Oh, my God.

20:09.431 --> 20:12.468
We're one blood test away
from being pregnant.

20:12.500 --> 20:14.302
You ready for the news?

20:14.336 --> 20:16.505
I know the news.

20:16.538 --> 20:18.574
We're not.

20:18.606 --> 20:20.209
I, uh,

20:20.241 --> 20:22.644
cheated and took one of the tests.

20:22.677 --> 20:25.213
I peeked at the end.

20:27.982 --> 20:29.984
How are you not a giant
puddle of tears right now?

20:30.018 --> 20:31.787
Oh, I was,

20:31.819 --> 20:35.456
and if it weren't for
Eddie, I still would be.

20:35.490 --> 20:37.092
Eddie who?

20:37.125 --> 20:39.461
Eddie your father.

20:39.493 --> 20:41.863
I, um, did my best to hide it,

20:41.896 --> 20:43.331
you know, to keep it inside,

20:43.365 --> 20:46.234
but he took one look at me and he knew.

20:46.268 --> 20:48.837
Yeah, well, he's always been
very good at reading people.

20:48.869 --> 20:50.271
It's what makes him a good con man.

20:50.305 --> 20:53.108
He wasn't conning me. He was helping me.

20:53.141 --> 20:55.311
Yeah, so you would tell
me and I'd forgive him.

20:55.344 --> 20:57.011
That's what he does. He's
always working an angle.

20:57.045 --> 20:58.681
You cannot trust my father, Paige.

20:58.713 --> 21:01.082
Okay.

21:01.115 --> 21:03.251
You have so much anger towards him,

21:03.285 --> 21:05.154
and I get it,

21:05.186 --> 21:07.956
but you have to figure
out how to let that go

21:07.990 --> 21:11.859
because I want a family...
a happy family...

21:11.893 --> 21:13.929
and that can't happen with you carrying

21:13.962 --> 21:16.198
your anger around all the time.

21:18.066 --> 21:19.268
Look,

21:19.300 --> 21:22.837
I was ready to just give
up on IVF completely,

21:22.871 --> 21:25.841
but after one pep talk with Eddie,

21:25.874 --> 21:28.344
I want to sign up for
another round or two

21:28.376 --> 21:29.544
or ten.

21:29.577 --> 21:31.814
Whatever it takes.

21:51.333 --> 21:53.302
I'm gonna sit down.

21:57.606 --> 21:58.673
Hello.

21:58.706 --> 22:01.075
- Rosé?
- Yeah, sure.

22:01.108 --> 22:02.778
Would your guest like rosé?

22:02.810 --> 22:05.947
Uh, actually, you can
clear that setting.

22:05.981 --> 22:08.116
My date couldn't make it
to the rehearsal dinner.

22:08.150 --> 22:10.786
- Oh.
- Traffic.

22:10.818 --> 22:13.122
I don't have a date.

22:24.633 --> 22:28.069
You look like a guy who could
use a drink, and I'm buying.

22:28.103 --> 22:30.105
I think it's an open bar.

22:30.137 --> 22:31.606
Then I've got the next round too.

22:31.640 --> 22:32.975
What's the matter?

22:33.008 --> 22:35.678
No fun being stag at a wedding?

22:35.711 --> 22:37.613
Think everyone's looking at you?

22:37.645 --> 22:39.714
Wondering "What's wrong
with that loser?"

22:39.748 --> 22:42.217
Actually, I wasn't, but now I am.

22:42.250 --> 22:44.819
Please, I've been to
enough weddings on my own

22:44.853 --> 22:46.188
to know what you're feeling,

22:46.221 --> 22:48.390
and those are just Newberg's weddings.

22:50.192 --> 22:51.859
It would be nice to go to a wedding once

22:51.893 --> 22:53.629
with someone I love,

22:53.662 --> 22:55.497
but that's not what's bothering me.

22:55.529 --> 22:58.399
I've got some bad news.

22:58.433 --> 23:02.871
The test ruled out other
causes for your symptoms.

23:02.904 --> 23:04.873
I have Alzheimer's?

23:04.905 --> 23:07.442
It's more likely, but
it's not a certainty.

23:07.475 --> 23:08.843
Now, I found a neurologist in London

23:08.876 --> 23:11.180
who comes highly recommended.

23:11.212 --> 23:12.714
I'm so sorry I can't help you more.

23:12.748 --> 23:16.785
Hey, you don't get to be more
upset about this than I do.

23:16.817 --> 23:18.487
No one likes a scene-stealer.

23:18.519 --> 23:19.887
Oh.

23:19.921 --> 23:21.190
Well, let's cheer you up.

23:21.222 --> 23:23.658
I've seen a lot of
attractive women here.

23:23.692 --> 23:25.760
So what's your thing, boobs?

23:25.794 --> 23:27.563
Butts?

23:27.596 --> 23:30.766
Something weirder?

23:30.798 --> 23:34.001
♪ There is always a silver lining ♪

23:34.035 --> 23:35.269
Silver lining?

23:35.302 --> 23:38.339
♪ You're a single,
cute, male physician ♪

23:38.373 --> 23:39.540
That's not helping.

23:39.574 --> 23:43.479
♪ You made encephalopathy
sound inviting ♪

23:43.511 --> 23:46.714
♪ With a warm, cheery disposition ♪

23:46.748 --> 23:48.217
Still not helping.

23:48.250 --> 23:51.819
♪ There are ills that
are quite ill-fated ♪

23:51.853 --> 23:55.791
♪ And at my age, I've had a few ♪

23:55.824 --> 23:59.027
♪ But though my memory
is quite deflated ♪

23:59.059 --> 24:06.268
♪ There's no way I'll forget you ♪

24:07.802 --> 24:11.372
♪ The good news is,
you're going to be okay ♪

24:11.405 --> 24:13.241
♪ The good news is ♪

24:13.275 --> 24:15.043
♪ Disease happens every day ♪

24:15.076 --> 24:18.480
♪ And you're the one they're
going to call and say ♪

24:18.512 --> 24:21.716
♪ Make me better ♪

24:21.750 --> 24:25.820
♪ A perfect score, who
gives a crap anyway? ♪

24:25.854 --> 24:29.324
♪ Microvascular changes
sure ain't child's play ♪

24:29.356 --> 24:30.826
♪ Heal thyself ♪

24:30.858 --> 24:33.595
♪ Or whatever it is they say, Doc ♪

24:37.132 --> 24:39.201
♪ I made belts from animal hide ♪

24:39.233 --> 24:40.234
Yeah.

24:40.268 --> 24:43.271
♪ I thought I had an STD ♪

24:43.305 --> 24:44.472
Right.

24:44.506 --> 24:47.776
♪ We tested positive for syphilis ♪

24:47.808 --> 24:51.579
♪ I packed my bags, that was it for me ♪

24:51.613 --> 24:54.449
♪ But then you said, "No,
it's Hansen's disease" ♪

24:54.481 --> 24:55.750
It was.

24:55.783 --> 24:58.820
♪ Leprosy ♪

24:58.854 --> 25:01.423
- Yeah.
- ♪ You made us well ♪

25:01.455 --> 25:03.491
♪ And saved our marriage ♪

25:03.525 --> 25:06.862
♪ Today is our fifth anniversary ♪

25:06.894 --> 25:10.766
♪ You said, "The good news is,
you're going to be okay ♪

25:10.798 --> 25:12.634
♪ So go have sex" ♪
- I don't think...

25:12.666 --> 25:14.269
♪ "Get pregnant this very day" ♪

25:14.301 --> 25:17.905
♪ Now we have twins and
one more is on the way ♪

25:17.939 --> 25:21.543
♪ And you're the reason ♪

25:21.576 --> 25:23.644
- ♪ Dr. Lawson
- Hank.

25:23.677 --> 25:25.079
♪ You're gonna be okay ♪

25:25.113 --> 25:26.815
- ♪ Dr. Hank ♪
- Just Hank.

25:26.847 --> 25:28.683
♪ You always save the day ♪

25:28.717 --> 25:30.352
♪ Thank you, Hank ♪

25:30.385 --> 25:34.222
♪ That's what we came here to say ♪

25:36.090 --> 25:38.659
♪ I had hypertensive nephropathy ♪

25:38.692 --> 25:39.894
Yeah, you did.

25:39.927 --> 25:41.295
♪ You knew it was licorice poisoning ♪

25:41.328 --> 25:43.464
♪ Not hyporeflexia ♪
- Well...

25:43.498 --> 25:46.434
♪ I had somatic skeletal
neuromuscular dysfunction ♪

25:46.468 --> 25:47.536
Yeah, I know.

25:47.568 --> 25:50.071
♪ Who are you? Where is Divya? ♪

25:50.105 --> 25:52.207
- Sorry.
- ♪ I had a CSF leak ♪

25:52.240 --> 25:54.276
♪ And cannabinoid
hyperemesis ♪ That's right.

25:54.308 --> 25:57.045
♪ I still don't know what
the hell that means ♪

25:57.077 --> 25:58.314
I'll explain it later.

25:58.346 --> 26:00.883
♪ You diagnosed me with hydrocephalus ♪

26:00.915 --> 26:04.519
♪ You blamed it
on my family genes ♪

26:04.551 --> 26:06.320
♪ But the good news is ♪

26:06.354 --> 26:08.390
♪ We're going to be okay ♪

26:08.423 --> 26:09.991
♪ The good news is ♪

26:10.025 --> 26:11.860
♪ We're living our life today ♪

26:11.893 --> 26:13.127
♪ So don't get down ♪

26:13.161 --> 26:15.397
♪ Turn that frown the other way ♪

26:15.430 --> 26:19.034
♪ And join the chorus ♪

26:19.067 --> 26:22.503
♪ Ignore the ills and spills
that are on display ♪

26:22.537 --> 26:25.941
♪ Life is not an
all-you-can-eat buffet ♪

26:25.973 --> 26:27.742
♪ But trust us, Hank ♪

26:27.776 --> 26:31.712
♪ For we'd never lead you astray ♪

26:33.647 --> 26:36.751
♪ You can't save everyone ♪

26:36.785 --> 26:40.956
♪ Even if you try ♪

26:40.989 --> 26:42.658
♪ 'Cause last I checked ♪

26:42.691 --> 26:47.462
♪ It's still quite certain
that we're gonna die ♪

26:47.494 --> 26:52.066
♪ We're all gonna die ♪

26:53.835 --> 26:56.038
♪ But the good news is ♪

26:56.070 --> 26:58.205
♪ We're going to be okay ♪

26:58.239 --> 27:00.241
♪ The good news is ♪

27:00.275 --> 27:02.177
♪ They're finding cures every day ♪

27:02.210 --> 27:05.814
♪ But you're the one we're
going to call and say ♪

27:05.846 --> 27:09.183
♪ "Make us better" ♪

27:09.217 --> 27:12.888
♪ So smile and read our
file without delay ♪

27:12.921 --> 27:16.424
♪ Run those tests and
please, don't make us pay ♪

27:16.458 --> 27:17.993
♪ And Hank, just say ♪

27:18.026 --> 27:23.565
♪ That good news is on the way ♪

27:23.597 --> 27:30.806
♪ But even if the sky is dark and gray ♪

27:30.838 --> 27:32.840
♪ The good news is ♪

27:34.642 --> 27:38.580
♪ The good news is, we're
all gonna be okay ♪

27:38.613 --> 27:39.981
♪ The good news is ♪

27:40.015 --> 27:42.017
♪ We're all gonna be okay ♪

27:42.049 --> 27:43.518
♪ The good news is ♪

27:43.550 --> 27:45.453
♪ We're all gonna be okay ♪

27:45.487 --> 27:46.989
♪ The good news is ♪

27:47.021 --> 27:48.923
♪ We're all gonna be okay ♪

27:48.956 --> 27:50.524
♪ The good news is ♪

27:50.558 --> 27:52.361
♪ We're all gonna be okay ♪

27:52.394 --> 27:54.061
♪ The good news is ♪

27:54.095 --> 27:55.998
♪ We're
all gonna be ♪...

27:57.331 --> 27:59.233
Annette.

28:00.234 --> 28:02.036
Annette.

28:02.069 --> 28:03.337
Annette. Annette. Easy, easy.

28:03.371 --> 28:06.541
You're having a seizure.

28:06.574 --> 28:08.143
Okay. Okay.

28:20.154 --> 28:21.717
You're missing the wedding.

28:21.842 --> 28:23.043
It doesn't start for an hour

28:23.077 --> 28:25.046
and I wanted to see you first.

28:25.079 --> 28:28.550
What a gentleman. I'm honored.

28:28.582 --> 28:31.919
So your EEG demonstrated slow waves

28:31.953 --> 28:34.122
in the right posterior
temporal zone of your brain,

28:34.155 --> 28:37.292
affecting the occipital
and temporal lobes.

28:37.324 --> 28:41.095
Have you noticed any auditory
or visual changes recently?

28:41.128 --> 28:43.397
I've been seeing numbers.

28:43.430 --> 28:46.333
Uh, digits, complex numbers?

28:46.367 --> 28:49.370
Who do I look like, Stephen Hawking?

28:49.404 --> 28:52.607
Numbers, like the ones
from movies and shows

28:52.639 --> 28:54.042
I've been in.

28:54.074 --> 28:55.843
Singing and dancing, some of which,

28:55.877 --> 28:59.347
I have to say, could use
a little more rehearsal.

28:59.379 --> 29:01.917
Wait, so you've been
having hallucinations?

29:01.949 --> 29:05.119
Like a beautiful waltz down memory lane.

29:05.153 --> 29:07.689
I wish you'd told me sooner.
They're a symptom.

29:07.722 --> 29:10.292
That my memories, along with my career,

29:10.324 --> 29:11.926
are ending?

29:11.959 --> 29:15.029
Hallucinations are not a
symptom of Alzheimer's.

29:15.062 --> 29:17.732
- They're not?
- Neither are seizures.

29:17.764 --> 29:20.267
I think you have a form of epilepsy.

29:20.301 --> 29:21.703
I'm gonna give you some medication

29:21.735 --> 29:23.138
and I'd like to forward your records

29:23.170 --> 29:24.538
to the neurologist in London.

29:24.571 --> 29:26.974
Forward away.

29:27.007 --> 29:28.843
Can I get a doctor's note

29:28.877 --> 29:31.279
to attend a wedding?

29:31.311 --> 29:34.482
I've never missed one
of Toots' nuptials.

29:34.514 --> 29:37.651
Uh, I'm sorry, did you say, "Toots"?

29:37.685 --> 29:39.788
Let's keep that between you and me.

29:39.820 --> 29:41.022
Done and done.

29:41.054 --> 29:42.289
First, let's get you an MRI,

29:42.322 --> 29:43.724
make sure there are no other issues,

29:43.757 --> 29:45.559
but while we await the results,

29:45.592 --> 29:47.595
I see no reason why the maid of honor

29:47.628 --> 29:50.432
can't attend the wedding of Ms.
Toots Newberg.

30:02.176 --> 30:04.178
Hank's not here yet, huh?

30:07.581 --> 30:09.318
He's on his way.

30:21.061 --> 30:23.764
I prepared a speech for you,

30:23.798 --> 30:25.634
basically because Hank

30:25.667 --> 30:28.703
forced me to.

30:28.735 --> 30:30.437
I was gonna do it at
the rehearsal dinner,

30:30.471 --> 30:32.240
but, uh,

30:32.272 --> 30:33.808
then it got interrupted,

30:33.840 --> 30:35.644
so...

30:42.951 --> 30:45.353
Would you like to hear it now?

30:45.386 --> 30:48.290
I think I'm gonna need that drink first.

30:51.024 --> 30:52.360
Thank you.

30:56.965 --> 30:59.301
To my dad,

30:59.333 --> 31:01.135
Eddie R. Lawson,

31:01.168 --> 31:03.671
the man who made me who I am,

31:03.705 --> 31:05.907
good and bad.

31:05.939 --> 31:08.342
The same hustle,

31:08.376 --> 31:11.012
the attraction to shortcuts,

31:11.044 --> 31:15.215
the eye for a way in and up,

31:15.249 --> 31:16.718
but also the luck of finding people

31:16.751 --> 31:20.589
who love us for who we are
and make us better men.

31:24.993 --> 31:29.063
It breaks my heart when you
don't live up to the good, Dad,

31:29.097 --> 31:33.301
'cause if you can't live
up to it, how can I?

31:33.333 --> 31:36.304
And you have so much good in you.

31:38.906 --> 31:41.209
For me,

31:41.242 --> 31:43.011
purely because of my wife

31:43.043 --> 31:44.778
and my marriage,

31:44.811 --> 31:47.815
I have more confidence
in being my better self,

31:47.849 --> 31:50.185
being the guy with integrity

31:50.217 --> 31:53.287
who listens and learns

31:53.320 --> 31:55.889
and is happy.

31:55.923 --> 31:57.759
So...

31:57.792 --> 32:01.228
it's my hope that your marriage
brings you the same, Dad.

32:03.363 --> 32:06.167
I love you. Mazel tov.

32:06.199 --> 32:08.202
I love you.

32:11.505 --> 32:13.207
Mazel tov.

32:16.444 --> 32:21.349
I could not have asked for
a better wedding present.

32:21.381 --> 32:22.883
Dad, you know you pushed it too far

32:22.917 --> 32:24.019
when even with your health scare

32:24.051 --> 32:25.419
Evan wouldn't come around.

32:25.453 --> 32:28.089
The health scare made
it worse, actually.

32:28.121 --> 32:29.724
What if we lost you

32:29.756 --> 32:30.758
without even saying good-bye?

32:30.792 --> 32:33.261
Like, I can't do that again.

32:33.293 --> 32:34.595
Again?

32:34.628 --> 32:35.964
You were there for your mom.

32:35.996 --> 32:37.564
No, I wasn't. Not at the end.

32:37.598 --> 32:39.200
Sure you were.

32:39.233 --> 32:41.136
No, I wasn't.

32:41.168 --> 32:43.037
That last night at the
hospital, you went alone.

32:43.070 --> 32:44.672
You said you didn't want
me to see her like that.

32:44.705 --> 32:48.309
Remember?

32:48.341 --> 32:51.311
Evan, I'm so sorry.

32:51.345 --> 32:52.647
I thought I was protecting you.

32:52.679 --> 32:55.149
I know. It's okay.

32:55.183 --> 32:56.651
I'm the one who should be sorry.

32:56.684 --> 32:59.287
I made you do...

32:59.320 --> 33:00.487
an adult's job.

33:00.521 --> 33:03.224
You were such a little boy.

33:03.256 --> 33:04.426
Come here.

33:11.532 --> 33:14.769
All right, here's my promise:

33:14.801 --> 33:18.772
I will never take my sons'

33:18.805 --> 33:21.875
love for granted.

33:21.908 --> 33:24.278
Hmm.

33:28.337 --> 33:30.312
Marriage is a promise

33:30.337 --> 33:33.140
between two people who love each other,

33:33.376 --> 33:34.778
who trust that love,

33:34.953 --> 33:37.655
who honor one another as individuals

33:37.680 --> 33:39.749
in that togetherness,

33:39.781 --> 33:44.619
and who wish to spend the
rest of their lives together.

33:44.653 --> 33:47.924
Will you have this man
to be your husband,

33:47.956 --> 33:51.560
to live together in the
covenant of marriage?

33:52.728 --> 33:54.564
Mazel tov!

34:01.803 --> 34:03.605
You know, this is all
because of you, Hank.

34:03.638 --> 34:06.475
If you hadn't fixed my
flat tire way back then,

34:06.508 --> 34:08.743
I never would have met my sweet Eddie.

34:08.775 --> 34:11.914
Well, it was and is my pleasure.

34:11.946 --> 34:13.915
You were Newparts Newberg back then.

34:13.947 --> 34:15.550
And you were a citiot,

34:15.583 --> 34:17.620
but not anymore.

34:17.652 --> 34:20.022
Nice castle for a wedding.

34:20.054 --> 34:22.225
Do I get to meet the infamous owner?

34:22.257 --> 34:25.025
Uh, Boris and Marissa said
they were coming, but...

34:25.060 --> 34:27.597
Well, they sent a gift,
a very heavy gift.

34:27.629 --> 34:28.731
Like a brick.

34:28.763 --> 34:31.166
We haven't opened it yet.

34:31.199 --> 34:35.538
Brick heavy or gold bar heavy?

34:35.571 --> 34:37.206
I will be right back.

34:40.507 --> 34:45.146
I know it hasn't been easy
right now for you and Paige,

34:45.179 --> 34:47.549
but you've been a good
husband to my daughter

34:47.581 --> 34:50.085
and I just wanted to thank you.

34:50.118 --> 34:52.987
I underestimated you.

34:53.022 --> 34:55.224
Thank you, General Collins.

34:55.255 --> 34:57.726
And I know you'll be a good father

34:57.760 --> 35:00.897
to our grandchild,

35:00.930 --> 35:02.298
whenever that happens.

35:02.330 --> 35:04.499
That means a lot,

35:04.533 --> 35:07.703
especially coming from you, sir.

35:07.736 --> 35:08.838
Maybe it's time I call
you by your first name.

35:08.870 --> 35:10.238
What do you think?

35:10.272 --> 35:14.110
I don't think so, son.

35:14.142 --> 35:15.810
Kind of like our wedding.

35:15.843 --> 35:16.811
Yeah.

35:16.845 --> 35:18.981
Minus a couple of hundred guests,

35:19.013 --> 35:20.448
90% of the budget, and the castle,

35:20.481 --> 35:22.150
it's just like it.

35:22.184 --> 35:24.754
And I wouldn't have changed a thing.

35:24.787 --> 35:26.289
Me neither.

35:29.290 --> 35:32.562
I'll go get us some drinks.

35:45.374 --> 35:47.577
- Are you having fun?
- I am.

35:47.609 --> 35:51.012
Thank you for bringing me.
It's a beautiful wedding.

35:51.046 --> 35:53.515
Well, it's no Garden of Zall.

35:55.249 --> 35:57.786
It's gorgeous, and...

35:57.819 --> 35:59.321
it's very romantic.

36:12.234 --> 36:14.703
May I have everyone's attention?

36:14.736 --> 36:18.173
My spouse, my groom, my lover,

36:18.207 --> 36:19.809
it's time for us to dance,

36:19.841 --> 36:22.544
but first, I want to introduce you all

36:22.577 --> 36:24.713
to a very dear friend of mine,

36:24.747 --> 36:27.850
world-famous violinist, Mr. Joshua Bell.

36:27.883 --> 36:29.785
Thank you, Ms. Newberg, it's...

36:29.818 --> 36:31.754
it's always great to play
at one of your weddings.

36:31.787 --> 36:33.388
Congratulations to you both.

36:33.421 --> 36:35.724
Thank you.

36:35.758 --> 36:36.993
Here you go.

